## Conversation
User asked "in our tests, why do we need wandb service?". I traced it to the
`Start wandb service` step (W&B `local-testcontainer`) that test.yaml + the
nightly workflows start next to ClickHouse. User then said "try removing the
wandb service and see if the tests pass" and, after the experiment came back
green, "ok get rid of it" followed by "put this up as draft".

## Actions
- Mapped the wandb-service usage: `.github/workflows/{test,nightly-tests,
  nightly-replicated-leg}.yaml` each had an `Authenticate to Google Cloud`
  (WIF) step feeding a `docker login` + `docker run ... local-testcontainer`
  `Start wandb service` step, plus `WB_SERVER_HOST: http://localhost` env and
  an `id-token: write` permission.
- Built a py3.12 venv (uv), ran core trace shards locally against the existing
  ClickHouse container with CI-like env and NO wandb container:
    trace (-m trace_server): 956 passed / 20 skipped / 2 env flakes
    flow  (-m trace_server): 61 passed / 320 skipped / 0 failed
    trace_server_bindings:   55 passed
    trace_server (+shared):  1341 passed / 1 skipped
- Root-caused the 2 trace flakes: test_sync_eval_parallelism (assert <8s under
  16-worker load; passes solo) and test_flask_server (hardcodes port 6789;
  netstat showed another process LISTENing — werkzeug EADDRINUSE -> sys.exit).
  Six flow failures appeared only when running the FULL flow dir unmarked; all
  six are deselected by CI's `-m trace_server` and have no wandb code path
  (missing client fixture -> local WeaveInitError; one uses MagicMock server).
- Removed the wandb service + orphaned scaffolding from all 3 workflows
  (102 line deletions). Validated: python yaml.safe_load OK x3; actionlint has
  zero structural errors (only pre-existing shellcheck notes in untouched run
  blocks).

## Errors & Mistakes
- First combined background run used `PY=\"uv run ... pytest\"; \$PY tests/...`.
  zsh does NOT word-split unquoted parameter expansions, so \$PY was treated as
  one command name -> `command not found` (exit 127), nothing ran. Fixed by
  writing the command out explicitly per shard.
- Tried to edit MEMORY.md before Read-ing it in this session -> \"File has not
