## Hints for Future Agents
- `WB_SERVER_HOST` is NOT read by the weave Python client (it resolves the W&B
  host from `WANDB_BASE_URL`). It was inert in these jobs.
- nox forwards only a fixed env allowlist to the trace shards (noxfile ~L148);
  `WANDB_API_KEY` is intentionally absent except for `scorers` (W&B Artifacts).
- ch-image.sh pulls ClickHouse from GHCR via GITHUB_TOKEN; it never needed the
  GCP/WIF auth. That auth step existed ONLY for the wandb image docker login.
- Codecov uses CODECOV_TOKEN, not OIDC, so removing `id-token: write` is safe.
- NOT validated locally: integration provider shards (openai/anthropic/...)
  and `scorers`. They SHOULD be fine (integrations = ClickHouse + VCR; scorers
  = prod Artifacts on api.wandb.ai, not the local container) but the real
  confirmation is this PR's full CI matrix. Watch those shards on the draft.

## Codebase Discoveries
- The `client` fixture (tests/conftest.py) + UserInjectingExternalTraceServer/
  DummyIdConverter (tests/trace_server/conftest.py) fully bypass the W&B
  control plane; the wandb container was vestigial for the core shards.

